middleware\n│   │   │   └── routes/\n│   │   │       ├── auth.ts     # Auth endpoints (register, login, verify)\n│   │   │       └── users.ts    # User CRUD endpoints\n│   │   └── tests/\n│   │       ├── auth.test.ts\n│   │       └── users.test.ts   # Contains unresolved merge conflict markers\n│   └── worker/                 # Background job processor\n│       ├── package.json\n│       ├── tsconfig.json\n│       ├── src/\n│       │   ├── index.ts        # Worker startup\n│       │   ├── scheduler.ts    # Job scheduler\n│       │   └── jobs/\n│       │       ├── sync.ts     # Data sync job\n│       │       └── cleanup.ts  # Cleanup job\n│       └── tests/\n│           ├── scheduler.test.ts\n│           ├── sync.test.ts\n│           └── cleanup.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. ROOT PACKAGE.JSON\n\n**File:** `/workspace/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-monorepo-disaster\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"description\": \"Monorepo recovery benchmark\",\n  \"workspaces\": [\"packages/*\"],\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc -b\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint packages/*/src/ packages/*/tests/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"check:circular\": \"madge --circular --extensions ts packages/\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"madge\": \"^8.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. ROOT TSCONFIG.JSON\n\n**File:** `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [],\n  \"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"packages/api\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/worker\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/core\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Issue:** References are in wrong build order (api and worker depend on core, so core should be first).\n\n---\n\n### 4. PACKAGE: @MONOREPO/CORE\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/packages/core`\n\n#### package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@monorepo/core\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./dist/index.js\",\n  \"types\": \"./dist/index.d.ts\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"zod\": \"3.19.0\",\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Issue:** Zod version is pinned to 3.19.0, but code uses `z.pipe()` which requires zod >= 3.22.\n\n#### tsconfig.json\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"composite\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### Source Files\n\n**src/index.ts** - Main export file\n- Exports types: User, CreateUserInput, UserFilters, Role, Permission\n- Exports user functions: registerUser, validateUser, getUserById, getAllUsers, canUserPerformAction\n- Exports validation: schemas and validation functions\n- Exports database functions: createDatabase, createTables, insertUser, findUserById, findAllUsers\n- Exports permissions: hasPermission, getAllPermissions, canManageUsers, canWrite, canDelete, requirePermission\n\n**src/types.ts** - Shared type definitions\n- Role: 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer'\n- Permission: 'read' | 'write' | 'delete' | 'manage_users' | 'view_reports'\n- User interface with id, name, email, role, createdAt, updatedAt\n- CreateUserInput interface\n- UserFilters interface\n- userExists() utility function\n\n**Issue:** `types.ts` imports `getUserById` from `user.js`, creating potential circular dependency.\n\n**src/database.ts** - SQLite database management\n- createDatabase(path): Creates better-sqlite3 database with WAL mode\n- createTables(conn): Creates users table with indexes\n- insertUser(conn, user): Inserts user and returns User object\n- findUserById(conn, id): Queries user by ID\n- findAllUsers(conn): Returns all users\n\n**src/user.ts** - User management business logic\n- getDefaultConnection(): Lazy-initializes in-memory database\n- resetDefaultConnection(): Closes default connection\n- registerUser(input): Validates and inserts user\n- validateUser(input): Validation wrapper\n- getUserById(id): Gets user from default connection\n- getAllUsers(): Gets all users from default connection\n- canUserPerformAction(userRole, action): Permission check wrapper\n\n**src/permissions.ts** - Role-based access control\n- ROLE_PERMISSIONS: Maps roles to permissions\n- hasPermission(role, permission): Checks if role has permission\n- getAllPermissions(role): Returns all permissions for role\n- canManageUsers(role): Checks manage_users permission\n- canWrite(role): Checks write permission\n- canDelete(role): Checks delete permission\n- requirePermission(role, permission): Throws if permission missing\n\n**src/validation.ts** - Zod schema validation\n- roleSchema: Validates 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer'\n- createUserSchema: Validates name, email, role\n- userIdSchema: Coerces string to positive integer using z.pipe()\n- userFiltersSchema: Validates filters with string-to-number coercion\n- validateCreateUser(): Safe parsing function\n- validateUserId(): Safe parsing function\n\n**Issue:** Uses `z.pipe()` which requires zod >= 3.22, but package.json pins zod to 3.19.0\n\n#### Test Files\n\n**tests/permissions.test.ts** - 6 tests\n- Admin has all permissions\n- Viewer can only read\n- Returns all permissions for role\n- canManageUsers permission check\n- canWrite permission check\n- canDelete permission check\n- requirePermission throws for missing permissions\n\n**tests/validation